{"title":"Archive.org, a repository of the history of the Internet, has a data breach","link":"https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/10/archive-org-a-repository-storing-the-entire-history-of-the-internet-has-been-hacked/","date":1728519176000,"content":"<p>Archive.org, possibly one of the only entities to attempt to preserve the entire history of the World Wide Web and much of the broader Internet, was recently compromised in a hack that revealed data on roughly 31 million users.</p>\n<p>A little after 2 pm California time, social media blew up with screenshots showing what the archive.org homepage displayed.</p>\n<figure>\n    <div>\n                        <div>\n            <div>\n              <a href=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/archive-hack.png\" target=\"_blank\">\n                <img width=\"756\" height=\"412\" src=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/archive-hack.png\" srcset=\"https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/archive-hack.png 756w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/archive-hack-300x163.png 300w, https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/archive-hack-640x349.png 640w\" />\n              </a>\n              <div>\n                \n                              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n                  </div>\n      </figure>\n\n<p>It read:</p><p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/10/archive-org-a-repository-storing-the-entire-history-of-the-internet-has-been-hacked/\">Read full article</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://arstechnica.com/information-technology/2024/10/archive-org-a-repository-storing-the-entire-history-of-the-internet-has-been-hacked/#comments\">Comments</a></p>","author":"Dan Goodin","siteTitle":"Ars Technica","siteHash":"5b0ddf6e8923e49262a7894cfd77962733e43fbcc565a103b48373820b310636","entryHash":"13e49d6335aed595dca77f0afea68c4e1c954ed513cbaeab38423f8fe5965b8a","category":"Tech